The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for identifying protein-protein interactions in abstracts and full-text documents. This falls under the domain of computational biology, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of linear models and support vector machines (SVMs) for classification tasks is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The feature expansion method based on word proximity networks involves analyzing the relationships between words in a text, which is a common technique in NLP (cs.CL). The use of singular value decomposition (SVD) is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and data analysis (cs.IR). Finally, the paper also deals with uncertainty-based integration, which is a technique used in decision-making and optimization problems, and could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
